Large pans of ice u/s released mid mmt (panel 10) caused backwater from ice jam d/s of gauge/control.  Mmnt not to be used for curve defining.  The ice jam caused the backwater effect to travel up stream past the gauge resulting in decreased discharge passing the gauge until the ice jam released.  This mimicks a shut off effect up stream.
